0.086476,0.07783,0.073033,0.06138,0.051913,0.047019],"unified_progress":[0.056968,0.086729,0.10113,0.11769,0.10757,0.10071,0.093464,0.086604,0.081067,0.066046,0.054271,0.047745]},{"section":5,"text":"That can definitely cause heartburn because it allows stomach acid to reflux more easily.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.05269,0.094403,0.098868,0.10017,0.099345,0.096651,0.093522,0.087921,0.07927,0.075944,0.064194,0.057019],"unified_progress":[0.058486,0.075208,0.084895,0.09135,0.094673,0.10085,0.095466,0.093617,0.088558,0.0847,0.072732,0.05946]},{"section":6,"text":"Now, looking at the endoscopic biopsy results: thickening of the basal layer of the squamous epithelium, upward extension of the papillae (which I think is called papillae elongation), and increased neutrophils and lymphocytes.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.060098,0.10556,0.10266,0.09839,0.093621,0.093125,0.088504,0.085048,0.082178,0.071446,0.062469,0.0569],"unified_progress":[0.061199,0.085433,0.093631,0.099417,0.10077,0.098267,0.094392,0.090255,0.086865,0.074321,0.062945,0.052504]},{"section":7,"text":"Hmm.","dimension":-1,"group":-1,"is_degenerate":true,"model_progress":[0.32754,0.05552,0.056479,0.064943,0.063683,0.063453,0.059806,0.066403,0.066686,0.061217,0.064944,0.049325],"unified_progress":[0.21874,0.087408,0.067676,0.066547,0.076837,0.073772,0.087232,0.079257,0.074512,0.060066,0.055338,0.052619]},{"section":8,"text":"I remember that in chronic\u80c3\u98df\u7ba1\u53cd\u6d41\u75c5 (GERD), there are specific histological changes.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.060371,0.12914,0.066976,0.1079,0.10299,0.10016,0.09019,0.081655,0.073689,0.068716,0.061797,0.056421],"unified_progress":[0.064379,0.092327,0.067292,0.099147,0.099875,0.10259,0.093652,0.092622,0.086498,0.080526,0.068181,0.05291]},{"section":9,"text":"Let me recall: in Barrett's esophagus, there's metaplasia with columnar epithelium, but that's not mentioned here.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039445,0.075948,0.088988,0.099147,0.1054,0.10393,0.10222,0.093084,0.083763,0.083425,0.066199,0.05845],"unified_progress":[0.041443,0.064007,0.086566,0.096,0.10125,0.1081,0.10328,0.099137,0.092996,0.086666,0.068169,0.052394]},{"section":10,"text":"The biopsy here talks about squamous epithelium changes.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042155,0.082352,0.092566,0.09689,0.096335,0.095269,0.094194,0.089704,0.089058,0.081958,0.073048,0.066471],"unified_progress":[0.04692,0.072311,0.086336,0.096609,0.10104,0.09969,0.097386,0.094365,0.092509,0.082533,0.071258,0.059042]},{"section":11,"text":"Wait, in chronic GERD, the esophagus can have changes like basal cell hyperplasia, where the basal layer of the squamous epithelium thickens.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.042078,0.077763,0.086414,0.095071,0.099102,0.099516,0.099203,0.092961,0.088562,0.083088,0.071127,0.065114],"unified_progress":[0.050222,0.06586,0.084156,0.094985,0.099889,0.10883,0.10142,0.0965,0.091909,0.082052,0.068017,0.056164]},{"section":12,"text":"The papillae of the lamina propria extending upward would create a sawtooth appearance, which is another sign of chronicity.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039951,0.080155,0.089275,0.095974,0.097314,0.098763,0.09763,0.091543,0.092337,0.081847,0.070594,0.064618],"unified_progress":[0.043775,0.070729,0.08922,0.099906,0.10518,0.10531,0.10105,0.095292,0.093302,0.078162,0.064357,0.053711]},{"section":13,"text":"The presence of increased neutrophils and lymphocytes might indicate inflammation, but in GERD, the inflammation is usually more about chronic changes rather than active inflammation.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034666,0.072032,0.084286,0.091598,0.095517,0.096859,0.099474,0.096192,0.092615,0.088419,0.079976,0.068368],"unified_progress":[0.042081,0.066799,0.081169,0.08976,0.096919,0.10018,0.09961,0.097662,0.094805,0.090241,0.078458,0.06232]},{"section":14,"text":"Although sometimes there can be a mixed inflammatory response.","dimension":12,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032689,0.068224,0.081059,0.088837,0.094362,0.096888,0.099163,0.098225,0.095969,0.091894,0.0829,0.069789],"unified_progress":[0.038581,0.067081,0.081524,0.091993,0.096921,0.098595,0.10022,0.098178,0.095345,0.093114,0.078784,0.059665]},{"section":15,"text":"Hiatal hernia is a risk factor for GERD, so combining the symptoms, the hernia, and the biopsy findings pointing to chronic esophageal changes, the most likely diagnosis here is chronic GERD with these histological changes.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034598,0.071562,0.085654,0.091867,0.091962,0.090545,0.091101,0.088629,0.08934,0.091152,0.083,0.09059],"unified_progress":[0.03768,0.060655,0.073461,0.086132,0.089189,0.092352,0.094245,0.093791,0.095076,0.094855,0.092167,0.090399]},{"section":16,"text":"The key points are the symptoms, the hernia contributing to reflux, and the biopsy showing basal hyperplasia and papillae changes, which are hallmarks of chronic GERD.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029772,0.062874,0.075988,0.083874,0.087956,0.090546,0.09337,0.092488,0.095864,0.095134,0.093822,0.098313],"unified_progress":[0.033394,0.054095,0.067688,0.079657,0.085614,0.091378,0.093223,0.095786,0.099787,0.099828,0.10048,0.099065]},{"section":17,"text":"I don't think it's something like esophagitis unless specified, but the biopsy details fit more with the chronic changes from GERD rather than acute inflammation.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028002,0.05876,0.071331,0.079079,0.084286,0.087471,0.092711,0.094919,0.09751,0.099409,0.097982,0.10854],"unified_progress":[0.030034,0.049742,0.062169,0.072606,0.079348,0.085495,0.090066,0.096739,0.10142,0.10651,0.11099,0.11488]},{"section":18,"text":"So putting it all together, the answer should be chronic gastroesophageal reflux disease, or GERD.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.025942,0.045851,0.052221,0.059228,0.067098,0.074486,0.082272,0.088532,0.097666,0.10292,0.11782,0.18596],"unified_progress":[0.026254,0.030516,0.037701,0.046556,0.052396,0.064483,0.069502,0.083613,0.09725,0.1099,0.15611,0.22572]}]}}